{
  "doc_id": "37344",
  "text": "Mutation analysis [CITATION_1] is widely used to assess the adequacy of a test suite and the effectiveness of testing techniques. It applies some mutation operators to seed various faults into the program under test, in order to generate a set of variants, namely mutants. If a test case causes a mutant to show a behavior different from the program under test, the mutant is said to be \"killed\".",
